What java developer do in microsoft?

Yes. Microsoft hires Java developers, especially for backend, cloud, distributed systems, and enterprise platforms. 
Even though Microsoft is famous for C# and .NET, Java is widely used by customers on Microsoft Azure. 
Microsoft therefore builds tools, services, and cloud infrastructure that support Java applications.

### What a Java developer at Microsoft typically does

* Build backend services — REST APIs, microservices, authentication systems, payment systems, etc.

* Work on cloud platforms — deploy and manage Java applications on Microsoft Azure.

* Develop distributed systems — scalable services that run across many servers.

* Optimize performance — memory usage, GC tuning, latency reduction.

* Use DevOps tools — Docker, Kubernetes, CI/CD pipelines.

* Write automated tests — unit, integration, and load tests.

* Collaborate with other teams — product managers, QA engineers, SREs, and frontend developers.

